\cdot \vec{h} + \vec{h} \cdot \vec{h}},$ where $\vec{b}$ is any basis vector of the base of the pyramid ( incidentally $\vec{h}$ is its height), and $\vec{h}$ is any height vector of the pyramid ( incidentally $\vec{b}$ is its basis vector). Combining all of this, the volume of the pyramid is $\frac{1}{3} \frac{1}{2} (\vec{C} - \vec{B}) \cdot \frac{1}{2}(\vec{E} - \vec{B}) \cdot \left| \vec{h} \right| = \frac{1}{16} \left| \vec{h} \right| = \frac{1}{16}.$</think>

